summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from Solomon Levinson and Rosa Levinson, his wife to the City of Seattle, dated the 24th day of January, 1907, to all of the unplatted tract in Government Lot 1, Section 6, T. 25 N. R. 4 E. lying between the south margin of Green Lake Boulevard and the center of Green Lake, between a southerly production of Wallingford Avenue and of the boundary line separating the lands of S. Levinson and W. D. Wood.
